{{wikipedia|dab=Perennial (disambiguation)|Perennial}}
==English==

===Etymology===
1644, from {{etyl|la}} {{term|perennis||lasting through the whole year}}, from {{term|per-||through}} + {{term|annus||year}}.

===Pronunciation===
* {{IPA|/pəˈɹɛniəl/}}, {{X-SAMPA|/p@"rEni@l/}}

===Adjective===
{{en-adj|-}}

# Lasting or remaining active throughout the [[year]], or all the time.
#: ''a '''perennial''' stream''
# {{botany|of a plant}} Having a life cycle of more than two years. Compare {{term|annual}}, {{term|biennial}}.
# {{figuratively}} Continuing without [[cessation]] or [[intermission]]; [[perpetual]]; [[permanent]]; [[unceasing]]; never [[failing]].
#* '''1790''', [[w:Edmund Burke|Edmund Burke]], ''[[s:Reflections on the Revolution in France|Reflections on the Revolution in France]]''
#*: The '''perennial''' existence of bodies corporate and their fortunes are things particularly suited to a man who has long views…
# {{figuratively}} [[enduring|Enduring]]; [[lasting]]; [[timeless]].
#: ''His artwork has a '''perennial''' beauty.''
# {{figuratively}} [[recurrent|Recurrent]]; appearing or recurring again and again.
#: ''Change is a '''perennial''' theme in politics.''

